# Safe Area & Keyboard Dismiss

## Safe area (no clipped headers)

- No interactive header (back, cancel, done, close) may sit under the status bar or notch.
- Full-screen `Modal`s must use `FullScreenModalShell` or `ModalSheetHeader` with `useSafeAreaInsets()` — never rely on bare `SafeAreaView` inside `Modal` alone.
- Bottom-sheet modals must apply `paddingBottom: insets.bottom` on the sheet card (and top inset on backdrop when full-height).
- Header actions: `minHeight: 48`, generous `hitSlop`, padding below `insets.top`.

## Keyboard dismiss

- Screens/lists with text inputs must use `DismissKeyboardScrollView`, `DismissKeyboardFlatList`, or spread `KEYBOARD_AWARE_SCROLL_PROPS` / `KEYBOARD_AWARE_LIST_PROPS` from `@/components/common`.
- Tap outside inputs dismisses keyboard (`KeyboardDismissView` wrapper).
- Tapping a field refocuses it: always set `keyboardShouldPersistTaps="handled"` on scrollables with inputs.
- Gorhom bottom sheets with inputs: `keyboardBehavior="interactive"`, `keyboardBlurBehavior="restore"`.

## Shared primitives (use these, do not reinvent)

| Primitive | Use when |
|-----------|----------|
| `FullScreenModalShell` | Full-screen modal with header |
| `ModalSheetHeader` | Cancel / title / Done row inside any modal |
| `KeyboardDismissView` | Wrap screen/modal body with inputs |
| `DismissKeyboardScrollView` | Scrollable form screens |
| `DismissKeyboardFlatList` | Search + list pickers |

## Definition of done

Any new screen or modal with inputs must use the shared primitives above. Manual check: header buttons fully visible and tappable on iOS and Android.
